OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F303A1737507298
OL,3,CHMRC 'degrading its own services as a
OL,4,Cmatter of policy'
OL,6,F"We will always be there to answer the
OL,7,Fphone for those who need extra help.
OL,8,FAt the same time, more than 80% of
OL,9,Fcustomers are satisfied with our
OL,10,Fdigital services, with more and more
OL,11,Fpeople using them to quickly and
OL,12,Feasily manage their tax affairs."
OL,14,FIt is understood that Mr Harra has
OL,15,Fwritten to the PAC to rebut the
OL,16,Fimplication that HMRC has deliberately
OL,17,Fmade its customer service worse.
OL,26,@nD@AOUtD@aO]
