OL,3,CHMRC 'degrading its own services as a
OL,4,Cmatter of policy'
OL,6,FCommittee chairman Sir Geoffrey
OL,7,FClifton-Brown said: "Given that
OL,8,Fcitizens have no choice but to engage
OL,9,Fwith HMRC, it has a responsibility to
OL,10,Faspire to the highest standards of
OL,11,Fservice.
OL,13,F"Unfortunately, what we have instead
OL,14,Fis a tax authority excavating its way
OL,15,Fto new lows in service levels every
OL,16,Fyear.
OL,26,@oD@UOUuD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/16
